        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 6:41PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of McDonald, or 13 miles northwest of Atwood, moving
south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of western Rawlins
County, including the following locations... Blakeman and Beardsley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
